<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<zabbix_export>
  <version>5.0</version>
  <date>2021-11-09T04:59:32Z</date>
  <groups>
    <group>
      <name>Access Points</name>
    </group>
  </groups>
  <templates>
    <template>
      <template>Meraki Access Points</template>
      <name>Meraki Access Points</name>
      <description>## Overview As I did not find any template to monitor my Meraki APs on the Meraki CLoud, here you are a template proposal I made. I have tested on my zabbix server and it works. the idea is to find all Meraki APs in the Cloud (SNMPv2-SMI::enterprises.29671.1.1.4.1.2) And each Meraki AP status (SNMPv2-SMI::enterprises.29671.1.1.4.1.3) (0-Down, 1-UP) With a Discovery List I add each AP as a Item Prototype and create a High trigger proto for each status. To make it work you must enable SNMP read on your MERAKI cloud: &lt;https://documentation.meraki.com/zGeneral_Administration/Monitoring_and_Reporting/SNMP_Overview_and_Configuration> The Template Needs as well a MACRO: {$SNMP\_MERAKI\_COMMUNITY} for the SNMP Comunity ## Author amendez</description>
      <groups>
        <group>
          <name>Access Points</name>
        </group>
      </groups>
      <discovery_rules>
        <discovery_rule>
          <name>APMERAKI</name>
          <type>SNMP_AGENT</type>
          <snmp_oid>discovery[{#ITEM.NAME},SNMPv2-SMI::enterprises.29671.1.1.4.1.2,{#ITEM.STATUS},SNMPv2-SMI::enterprises.29671.1.1.4.1.3]</snmp_oid>
          <key>APLIST</key>
          <delay>30s</delay>
          <item_prototypes>
            <item_prototype>
              <name>Name.{#ITEM.NAME}</name>
              <type>CALCULATED</type>
              <key>MerakiDeviceIndex.[{#SNMPINDEX}]</key>
              <delay>30s</delay>
              <params>{#ITEM.STATUS}</params>
            </item_prototype>
            <item_prototype>
              <name>{#ITEM.NAME}.Status:{#ITEM.STATUS}</name>
              <type>CALCULATED</type>
              <key>MerakiDeviceIndexStatus.[{#SNMPINDEX}]</key>
              <delay>30s</delay>
              <params>{#ITEM.STATUS}</params>
              <trigger_prototypes>
                <trigger_prototype>
                  <expression>{last()}=0</expression>
                  <name>{#ITEM.NAME}.Status</name>
                  <priority>HIGH</priority>
                  <tags>
                    <tag>
                      <tag>DOWN</tag>
                      <value>0</value>
                    </tag>
                    <tag>
                      <tag>UP</tag>
                      <value>1</value>
                    </tag>
                  </tags>
                </trigger_prototype>
              </trigger_prototypes>
            </item_prototype>
          </item_prototypes>
        </discovery_rule>
      </discovery_rules>
    </template>
  </templates>
</zabbix_export>